description:
Following the New 52 DC Comics event, The Story of the Green Lantern is reborn, with new twists and plots. Green Lantern is a monthly comic including some of the Corps most noticable members, alongside some new and formidable Green Lanterners. Major turning points within this comic are the Rise of the Third Army, the Revenge of Black Hand and the Introducton of Simon Baz.

Long time Green Lantern writer Geoff Johns follows where War of the Green Lanterns left off, Sinestro, long time enemy of the Green Lantern Corps, has become a Green Lantern again, and no one knows why. Meanwhile, Hal Jordan is still with out his ring, and due to his over commitment to the Corps, his civilian life back on Earth is in shambles.

deck: Meet Miles Morales, the all-new Ultimate Spider-Man!
description:
Ultimate Comics: Spider-Man Volume 2

Starring: Miles Morales as Spider-Man. Directly leading out of the events from Ultimate Comics Spider-Man Vol.1 and Ultimate Fallout in which the Death of Peter Parker was brought. Brian Michael Bendis brings a new Spider-Man to the world: 13 year-old Miles Morales. Bitten by a genetically altered spider, Miles gained the powers once possessed by the original plus more. The series ended with issue 28 and was continued in the Hunger mini-series and the Cataclysm: Ultimate Spider-Man mini-series after which it was then continued into a new series named Miles Morales: Ultimate Spider-Man. An issue 200 was published in this volume, counting all issues together from the 3 volumes.

Cast of Characters

Along with Miles Morales in the title role, we are welcoming a whole slew of friends and family into the Ultimate Spideyverse including Miles' parents plus roommates Ganke and Judge at the charter school they attend. Don't worry, villains are not neglected as we meet Miles's uncle Aaron as the Prowler and a reinvented Scorpion as a Mexican drug lord looking to be New York's next kingpin. Also appearing are familiar faces from past volumes and other series in the Ultimate Universe like Jessica Drew with the rest of SHIELD and Peter Parker's family: May Parker and Gwen Stacy.

Collected Editions

  • Ultimate Comics Spider-Man Vol. 1 (#1-5, Ultimate Fallout #4)
  • Secret Wars Prelude (#1)
  • Miles Morales: The Ultimate Spider-Man Ultimate Collection Book One (#1-12)
  • Ultimate Comics Spider-Man Vol. 2 (#6-10)
  • Ultimate Comics Spider-Man Vol. 3 (#11-18)
  • Ultimate Comics: Divided We Fall, United We Stand (#13-17)
  • Miles Morales: The Ultimate Spider-Man Ultimate Collection Book Two (#13-28 & 16.1)
  • Ultimate Comics Spider-Man Vol. 4 (#16.1 and #19-22)
  • Ultimate Comics Spider-Man Vol. 5 (#23-28)
  • Miles Morales: The Ultimate Spider-Man: Revival (#200)
  • Miles Morales: The Ultimate Spider-Man Ultimate Collection Book Three (#200)
name: Ultimate Comics Spider-Man
